==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it}} {{term|lang=it|dilettante}}, prop. present participle of {{term|dilettare||to delight}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|delectare||to delight}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Italian}} {{IPA|/diletˈtante/}}, {{SAMPA|/dilet"tante/}}
* {{a|RP}} {{enPR|dĭlĭtănʹtĭ}}, {{IPA|/dɪlɪˈtæntɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/dIlI"t{ntI/}}<!-- Please provide a reference for this erroneous pronunciation: {{a|Aus}} {{IPA|/dɪləˈtɔnt/}} before readding it to the entry. -->
; cf. [[dilettanti#Pronunciation]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dilettanti|pl2=(''rarely'') '''[[dilettantes]]'''}}

# An [[amateur]], someone who [[dabble]]s in a field out of casual interest rather than as a profession or serious interest.
# A person with a general but [[superficial]] interest in any art or a branch of [[knowledge]]. (Sometimes derogatory.)

